that our findings represent a bona-fide halo in M33,\nrather than extended emission from the disk substructure. We interpret our\nfindings in terms of an upper limit to M33's halo that is a few percent of its\ntotal luminosity, although its actual luminosity is likely much less.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Oct 2012 17:27:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-10-16"}
