{"id":"1210.4212","submitter":"Holger F. Hofmann","authors":"Holger F. Hofmann and Changliang Ren","title":"Direct observation of temporal coherence by weak projective measurements\n  of photon arrival time","comments":"7 pages, 1 figure, detailed description of count rate evaluation in\n  weak and strong limits has been added","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A 87, 062109 (2013)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.87.062109","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We show that a weak projective measurement of photon arrival time can be\nrealized by controllable two photon interferences with photons from short-time\nreference pulses at a polarization beam splitter. The weak value of the\nprojector on the arrival time defined by the reference pulse can be obtained\nfrom the coincidence rates conditioned by a specific output measurement. If the\nweak measurement is followed by a measurement of frequency, the coincidence\ncounts reveal the complete temporal coherence of the single photon\nwavefunction. Significantly, the weak values of the input state can also be\nobtained at higher measurement strengths, so that correlations between weak\nmeasurements on separate photons can be observed and evaluated without\ndifficulty. The method can thus be used to directly observe the non-classical\nstatistics of time-energy entangled photons.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Oct 2012 22:59:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 1 Mar 2013 03:44:06 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 8 May 2013 02:12:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-06-25"}
