 to the clear detection of some mini-flares\nsuperimposed on the flux variations during the night over timescales as short\nas 12 minutes. The detection of short timescale flux variability in the sources\nstudied here is clearly due to stronger time compression leading to the jets in\nthese sources having large Doppler factors, similar to that of the inner jets\nof TeV blazars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Oct 2012 12:47:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
